A Kenyan man who went missing in December last year has been found dead. The lifeless body of Brian Nyawade Owino, who went to Berlin, Germany in August 2017, was found at Ostkreuz train station. Brian went missing on December 29, 2017 and was found dead in Berlin on January 5. Circumstances of his death still remain unclear. Kenyan Community in Germany is currently fund raising to facilitate the transportation of his body back home. The community has so far raised Sh880,000 and is appealing to friends and well wishers to contribute for the course. The wish of his family in Kenya is for the body of Brian to be sent back home and laid to rest next to his mother's grave.